Surya ShahSurya Shah 3rd+Verified 3rd+ Global Marketing Expert | FRCI | Executive Director at Urban Infra Group | Founder & Director - BD at Natural Energy News | Passionate about social impact | Advocate for child health & poverty reductionGlobal Marketing Expert | FRCI | Executive Director at Urban Infra Group | Founder & Director - BD at Natural Energy News | Passionate about social impact | Advocate for child health & poverty reduction 4d 4 days ago Visible to anyone on or off LinkedIn
150 Years of Innovation Yet Classrooms Still Look the Same
This comparison is powerful.

 Phones have evolved beyond recognition.
 Cars have transformed completely.
 But classrooms? Theyve barely moved an inch.

The world has changed, yet education still follows a model built for factory workers not creative thinkers.
 Rows. Bells. Grades. Obedience over imagination.

If schools are meant to prepare students for the future, why do they still look like the past?

Its time to rebuild education around what truly makes us human:
 Critical thinking, not memorization
 Creativity, not conformity
 Human connection, not competition

Technology can automate almost everything except these three.

If we want the next generation to thrive, we must modernize education to nurture what machines cant:
 the human mind, the human heart, and the human spirit.

 How do you think we can begin transforming education for the world ahead?

 Follow Surya Shah for more updates and insights on Indias space, infrastructure, and technology breakthroughs.
